Altitude

 ggplot(frogs,aes(altitude,pres.abs)) +
   geom_point() +
   geom_smooth() +
   xlab ("Altitude") +
   ylab ("Probability of Presence")
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'

frogs$alt100 <- frogs$altitude/100
fit.1 <- glm(pres.abs~alt100, data=frogs, binomial(link="logit"))
autoplot(fit.1) 

x <- predict(fit.1)
y <- resid(fit.1)
binnedplot(x,y)

coef(fit.1)
## (Intercept)      alt100 
##   5.6331388  -0.3994036
confint(fit.1)
## Waiting for profiling to be done...
##                 2.5 %     97.5 %
## (Intercept)  2.122839  9.2875209
## alt100      -0.636625 -0.1719672
ggplot(frogs, aes(altitude, pres.abs)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method="glm", method.args=list(family="binomial"(link="logit")))+
  xlab ("Altitude")+
  ylab("Probability of Presence")
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'

Number of Breeding Pools

 ggplot(frogs,aes(NoOfPools,pres.abs)) +
   geom_point() +
   geom_smooth() +
   xlab ("# of Breeding Pools") +
   ylab ("Probability of Presence")
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'

frogs$NoPools100 <- frogs$NoOfPools/100
fit.2 <- glm(pres.abs~NoPools100, data=frogs, binomial(link="logit"))
autoplot(fit.2) 

x <- predict(fit.2)
y <- resid(fit.2)
binnedplot(x,y)

coef(fit.2)
## (Intercept)  NoPools100 
##   -0.888981    1.441371
confint(fit.2)
## Waiting for profiling to be done...
##                  2.5 %     97.5 %
## (Intercept) -1.3137017 -0.4880039
## NoPools100   0.3251617  2.6882528
ggplot(frogs, aes(NoOfPools, pres.abs)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method="glm", method.args=list(family="binomial"(link="logit")))+
  xlab ("# Breeding Pools")+
  ylab("Probability of Presence")
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'
